{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":5,"timestamp":1772458623,"nonce":"gvK1NCm9HI7YjzRLGSa7FXQ66X8=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOQ241x87vGAJezwAAAAVmcBqK"},"added":["enhancement"],"removed":[]},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772459084,"nonce":"YDDfH7wV9AVkf+88SxHv5BwOaxA=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87tfqK9","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/324#issuecomment-3984499389"},"message":"Note that there is already a setup script used for seting up repos. It and all it's references should be renamed before env is renamed.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772459408,"nonce":"LOTffbV4k1eZ45j0Jiq9ItHAIcY=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87tfxdJ","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/324#issuecomment-3984529225"},"message":"## Review\n\n### Scope Assessment\n\n**Well-scoped?** No — the owner's comment reveals a blocking prerequisite that significantly expands the scope: `.agent/scripts/setup.sh` already exists (it sets up workspace layers by cloning repos via vcstool). That script must be renamed first before `env.sh` can take the `setup` name. The current issue scope only describes the second phase.\n\n**Right repo?** Yes — workspace infrastructure, correctly placed.\n\n**Dependencies**: The existing `setup.sh` must be renamed and all its references updated before this issue can proceed. That predecessor work is not captured here. References to the existing `setup.sh` span:\n\n| File | References |\n|---|---|\n| `Makefile` | `setup-core`, `setup-all`, and 4 other targets |\n| `README.md` | Lines 84, 87, 133, 140 |\n| `AGENTS.md` | 1 reference |\n| `CLAUDE.md` | 1 reference |\n| `.github/copilot-instructions.md` | 1 reference |\n| `.agent/instructions/gemini-cli.instructions.md` | 1 reference |\n| `.agent/scripts/README.md` | ~8 references |\n| `.agent/scripts/bootstrap.sh` | 1 reference |\n| `.agent/scripts/health_check.sh` | 1 reference |\n| `.agent/scripts/env.sh` | 1 reference (internal comment) |\n| `.agent/knowledge/README.md` | 1 reference |\n| `.agent/work-plans/PLAN_ISSUE-303.md` | 2 references |\n\nThis is substantially more than the 4 files listed in the current issue scope.\n\n---\n\n### Principle Alignment\n\n| Principle | Status | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| Only what's needed | ✅ OK | Purely a rename — no new behaviour, no new tools |\n| A change includes its consequences | ⚠️ Watch | The issue lists 4 files to update for `env.sh`, but the prerequisite `setup.sh` rename has ~12+ references not yet captured in scope |\n| Enforcement over documentation | ⚠️ Watch | The checkout guardrail in `env.sh` is enforcement. The issue acknowledges this, but the scope item 4 (compatibility shim) should be resolved as a concrete decision, not left open |\n| Improve incrementally | ✅ OK | Small, focused change once the two phases are clearly separated |\n| Human control and transparency | ✅ OK | Renaming to match ROS workspace conventions improves discoverability |\n\n---\n\n### ADR Applicability\n\n| ADR | Triggered | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| 0002 — Worktree isolation | ✅ Yes | Implementation must use a worktree |\n| 0006 — Shared AGENTS.md | ✅ Yes | Script reference table in `AGENTS.md` and all three framework adapters must be updated — issue explicitly acknowledges this |\n| 0004/0005 — Enforcement hierarchy | ⚠️ Watch | `env.sh` is part of the enforcement layer; rename must not break the guardrail |\n\n---\n\n### Consequences\n\n- **Phase 0 (prerequisite, not yet scoped)**: Rename existing `setup.sh` → `\u003cnew-name\u003e` and update all ~12 references above. A good candidate name would clarify its purpose: `install.sh` or `init.sh` or `import_layers.sh` (it clones repos and runs vcstool — \"install\" mirrors `colcon build` → `install/` convention).\n- **Phase 1 (this issue)**: Rename `env.sh` → `setup.sh` and update 4 framework adapter files.\n- **Slash commands**: No `make_*` skills reference `env.sh` directly — no regeneration needed.\n- **Compatibility shim**: Decide concretely — a symlink `env.sh → setup.sh` is low-cost insurance for existing agent sessions that have `env.sh` sourced in shell history. Worth the one line.\n\n---\n\n### Recommendations\n\n1. **Expand scope or split into two issues**: Either update this issue to include the `setup.sh` prerequisite rename (with the full reference list above), or open a separate sub-issue (e.g. \"Rename setup.sh to install.sh to free the setup name\") and make this issue depend on it.\n2. **Decide on the target name for existing `setup.sh`**: `install.sh` is the most ROS-idiomatic candidate (mirrors the `install/` output directory convention); `init.sh` is also clear. This choice should be made explicitly — not left to the implementer.\n3. **Resolve the shim question explicitly**: Recommend adding a one-line forwarding shim `env.sh` that sources `setup.sh` with a deprecation warning, then removing it in a follow-up. This avoids breaking any agent that has `source .agent/scripts/env.sh` in its session history.\n4. **Update issue title**: If the target name is `setup.sh`, the title is correct. If the owner meant no extension (just `setup`), clarify — shell scripts sourced with `source` work with or without `.sh`, but consistency with ROS (`setup.bash`) might prefer `.bash` for sourced scripts.\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Copilot CLI Agent`\n**Model**: `claude-sonnet-4.6`","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772460233,"nonce":"Zj42+OMXNQxfDAwJF6qHie2RR0w=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87tgEUE","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/324#issuecomment-3984606468"},"message":"Decisions to incorporate into the implementation plan:\n\n- **Rename existing `setup.sh` → `setup_layers.sh`** (and update all references)\n- **New setup scripts should mimic ROS conventions**: provide both `setup.sh` and `setup.bash` so users can source whichever extension they prefer, matching the pattern ROS uses in `install/setup.sh` and `install/setup.bash`\n- **No compatibility shim needed** for the old `env.sh` path\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Copilot CLI Agent`\n**Model**: `claude-sonnet-4.6`","files":null},{"type":4,"timestamp":1772474182,"nonce":"ewjOx03MhKmj6Yq4VxWKI/EejvU=","metadata":{"github-id":"CE_lADOQ241x87vGAJezwAAAAVm5jH7"},"status":2}]}